<body>
    <h1>About StrumSpace</h1>
    <div class="outer">
        <section class="features">
            <!-- Feature 1 -->
            <div class="feature-row">
                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="/img/5.jpg" alt="Feature 1 Image">
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h2>Song Chord Library</h2>
                    <p> The Song Chord Library is a comprehensive repository of guitar chords for a vast range of songs. This feature allows users to easily search and browse through various chord progressions and arrangements tailored for popular tracks. With an intuitive admin panel, updates and new additions to the library are seamless, ensuring that users always have access to the latest chord charts. Whether you're a beginner learning the basics or an experienced player looking for intricate chord variations, this library is a valuable tool for enhancing your playing experience.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        
            <!-- Feature 2 -->
            <div class="feature-row reverse">
                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="/img/1.jpg" alt="Feature 2 Image">
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h2>Metronome</h2>
                    <p> The Metronome feature serves as a digital timing tool that helps musicians practice and maintain a steady tempo. It produces rhythmic clicks or beeps at set intervals, allowing users to keep their timing consistent while practicing scales, exercises, or songs. The metronome can be customized to different beats per minute (BPM) and time signatures, making it versatile for various musical styles and practices. It's an essential tool for developing rhythm skills, improving timing accuracy, and ensuring a more disciplined practice routine.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        
            <!-- Feature 3 -->
            <div class="feature-row">
                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="/img/6.jpg" alt="Feature 3 Image">
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h2>Fretboard Notes</h2>
                    <p>The Fretboard Notes feature provides an interactive visualization of the guitar fretboard, highlighting the locations of notes across different frets and strings. This tool helps musicians understand the spatial arrangement of notes, making it easier to navigate the fretboard and learn new scales and chords. By visualizing where each note is located, users can improve their ability to play by ear, compose music, and develop a deeper understanding of guitar theory. This feature is particularly beneficial for students and educators alike in the process of learning and teaching guitar.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        
            <!-- Feature 4 -->
            <div class="feature-row reverse">
                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="/img/4.webp" alt="Feature 4 Image">
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h2>Song Requests</h2>
                    <p>The Song Requests feature empowers users to actively participate in expanding the library of guitar chords by submitting their own song requests. Users can fill out a request form specifying the songs they're interested in, and the development team will work on providing the requested chord charts. This feature fosters community engagement by allowing users to contribute to the content and ensures that the library evolves based on user interests. It’s a great way to keep the content relevant and up-to-date with popular and emerging songs.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

                        <!-- Feature 5 -->
            <div class="feature-row">
                <div class="feature-image">
                    <img src="/img/3.jpg" alt="Feature 3 Image">
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h2>Chord Chart</h2>
                    <p>The Chord Chart feature offers detailed diagrams and visual representations of various guitar chords, showing finger positions and chord structures. This tool provides users with clear, easy-to-follow charts that are essential for learning and practicing different chords. Each chart typically includes information on chord variations, such as major, minor, and seventh chords, helping users build a diverse repertoire. Whether you’re just starting out or looking to refine your skills, these chord charts are a useful resource for improving technique and expanding your chord knowledge.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>


        </section>
    </div>
</body>



